CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1958, pg. A12, reads: "The FROGS Have Fun - Frog Week opened last Sunday with a gay party for members, their wives and out-of-town guests at the Terrain Room of Terrace Hall.  The above pictures tell the story of how the Frogs and their guests had fun...  The merry group in the center upper photo shows Dr. C. C. Blow and Robert M. Ratcliff, standing, as they join in the conversation of those seated below.  Left to right: Mrs. C. C. Blow, Mrs. Robert Ratcliffe, Mrs. Morris Fountain, Mrs. Clarence Waters and Mr. Fountain. ... - All Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Dr. C. C. Blow and Robert M. Ratcliffe standing behind Mrs. Blow, Mrs. Ratcliffe, Miriam Sharpe Fountain, Mrs. Waters, and Morris Fountain Sr. at FROGS week party in Terrain Room of Terrace Hall
